Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine red-brown. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 28a, 9, unless it is Montreal 2704.14. Name Apollodotos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0319.09.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0550)
